cjnOspfRouterId.name: cjnOspfRouterId
cjnOspfRouterId.description: OSPF router-id unique within an autonomous system

cjnOspfPathSplit.name: cjnOspfPathSplit
cjnOspfPathSplit.description: The number of OSPF path splits.

cjnOspfPeMax.name: cjnOspfPeMax
cjnOspfPeMax.description: Maximum number of path entries supported by OSPF

cjnOspfSpfState.name: cjnOspfSpfState
cjnOspfSpfState.description: Sets state of OSPF to enabled/disabled

cjnOspfAsbdrStatus.name: cjnOspfAsbdrStatus
cjnOspfAsbdrStatus.description: Sets flag for router to be as an Autonomous system boundary router enabled/disabled

cjnOspfAutoVLinkCreate.description: Sets flag for automatic creation of virtual link enabled/disabled

cjnOspfLocalExtType.description: Sets the metric type for local ext routes to 1 or 2

cjnOspfRipExtType.description: Sets the metric type for RIP ext routes to 1 or 2

cjnOspfSpfStaticExtType.description: Sets the metric type for static ext routes to 1 or 2

cjnOspfLowExtType.description: Sets the metric type for low preference static routes ext routes to 1 or 2

cjnOspfTraceFlags.name: cjnOspfTraceFlags
cjnOspfTraceFlags.description: Sets packet tracing for OSPF to on/off

cjnOspfGlobalStatsReset.name: cjnOspfGlobalStatsReset
cjnOspfGlobalStatsReset.description: When set to the value enable (1) all OSPF statistics are reset to zero after which the value of this MIB object returns to disable(2)

cjnOspfTOSCount.name: cjnOspfTOSCount
cjnOspfTOSCount.description: The number of types of services supported by OSPF.

cjnOspfRunSpf.description: Number of times the SPF calculation has been run

cjnOspfAbdrStatus.description: Shows the state of the router as an Area border router enabled/disabled

cjnOspfTxNewLsa.description: Shows the number of new link State Advertisements transmitted

cjnOspfRxNewLsa.description: Shows the number of new lsas received

cjnOspfRxHelloCnt.description: Shows number of hello messages received

cjnOspfTxHelloCnt.description: Shows number of hello messages transmitted

cjnOspfIfRowStatus.description: The Status of this entry in the table. Note the available states: active(1), -- Obviously Active on this interface. notInService(2) -- Configured on Interface but disabled. notReady(3), -- Interface entry NOT FULLY configured. createAndGo(4), -- NOT SUPPORTED. createAndWait(5) or destroy(6)

cjnOspfIfAreaId.description: The id of the area in which interface has been configured

cjnOspfIfMask.description: The network mask for the ip network the interface belongs to

cjnOspfIfType.description: The media type of the interface ( bcast, point to point, point to multipoint )

cjnOspfIfCost.description: The cost associted with the interface used to determine the path cost when interface is used as a next hop

cjnOspfIfDrRouterId.description: The router id of the designated router on the network the interface belongs to

cjnOspfIfDrIpAddr.description: The ip address of the interface on which packets are received from the designated router for the network the interface belongs to

cjnOspfIfBDrRouterId.description: The router id of the back up designated router on the network the interface belongs to

cjnOspfIfDrState.description: The designated router status of the interface ( DR, BDR or NoDR )

cjnOspfIfHelloTimer.description: The value of Hello timer for the interface with a default value of 10 seconds

cjnOspfIfDeadInterval.description: The value of dead interval timer for the interface with a default value of 40 seconds

cjnOspfIfRtrPriority.description: The interface priority used in the designated router election on the network the interface belongs to

cjnOspfIfTransitDelay.description: The delay in the packet transmission via the interface (default value is 1 second)

cjnOspfIfAuthKey.description: An eight character long simple password used for simple authentication type on an interface if authentication type is set to one. All the interfacew with OSPF enabled need to have the same authentication type to form adjacencies or exchange OSPF traffic

cjnOspfIfMd5KeyId.description: MD5 key id used for type 2 authentication on an OSPF interface

cjnOspfIfMd5KeyFlags.description: flags used for type 2 authentication on an OSPF interface

cjnOspfIfPollInterval.description: The value of Poll timer for the interface with a default value of 120 seconds
